      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Early morning: The conditions are generally favourable for ski touring. <br/> If there is cloud cover at night combined with warm air, the avalanche risk will already be 2 (moderate) by the morning because The surface of the snowpack will only just freeze. And so conditions in the mid-mountain range will already be somewhat unfavourable. <br/> In the late morning the natural activity of moist and wet avalanches will quickly increase. In particular in starting zones where no previous releases have taken place and on very steep slopes more medium-sized and, in isolated cases, large natural wet avalanches are to be expected. <br/> Backcountry tours and ascents to alpine cabins should be concluded timely. <br/> As a consequence of new snow and a sometimes moderate southeasterly wind, sometimes avalanche prone wind slabs formed on Monday. They have formed at high altitudes and in high Alpine regions.",
